  "script": "A tourist walked way too close to a wild bison for a photo, and it did not end well. The animal, which can weigh a ton and run three times faster than a person, lowered its head and charged in a blur. Bison look slow and calm, but they injure more people in national parks than any other animal, including bears. Rangers say to stay at least seventy-five feet back, but every year someone ignores it for a selfie. This time the tourist got tossed into the air and got lucky to walk away with only bruises. So why do people keep underestimating them?",
